    "guide": {
      "overview": "<h3><strong>Playstyle:</strong> Midrange with a bit of combo</h3><h3><strong>Difficulty:</strong> 5/10</h3><p><br></p><p>This deck is essentially a collection of two-card combos built on top of a solid midrange core that makes excellent use of Tawny.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>Core Combos:</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Tawny + Trinkets/Desserts</strong> – This enables efficient trades in the early game.</li><li><strong>Ring of Morrigan + Trinkets</strong> – In the right matchup, this combo can be game-breaking and provides an almost unfair advantage.</li><li><strong>Sir Agravaine + Frogs/Tawny</strong> – You can eliminate nearly any threat or bring your opponent’s Avatar to deathsdoor, as each Frog will deal 3 damage when attacking adjacent to Agravaine.</li><li><strong>Boudicca + Frogs/Tawny</strong> – Similar to Agravaine, playing Boudicca right after casting <em>Plague of Frogs</em> can be devastating.</li><li><strong>Ruler of Thul + Frogs</strong> – This was strong in Alpha and remains so.</li><li><strong>Manuscript + Frogs</strong> – Another combo that was effective in Alpha and still holds up.</li><li><strong>Pact with the Devil + Tawny</strong> – This synergy is amazing, but be mindful of the potential tempo loss.</li><li><strong>Snowball + Frogs/Tawny</strong> – Once you Frogball, you never go back! 😆</li><li><br></li></ul><h3><strong>Beast Package:</strong></h3><p>The Beast package is quite fun—it rarely makes a significant impact, but having a potential <em>Lugbog Cat</em> on turn 2 can be huge.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>Card Choices:</strong></h3><p><br></p><p>A lot of the card choices are debatable and come down to personal preference. Generally, water minions have a harder time making the cut compared to fire minions due to Jihad.</p><p>While many Druid lists run Drums of Doom, I personally see it as more of a trap. If you’ve reached a point where its effect is beneficial, you’re already behind. I’d rather have a card that helps maintain pressure.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>Sites:</strong></h3><p><br></p><p>Since the deck’s range is quite extreme and demanding, I don’t play a single site that doesn’t provide Threshold. So far, I’ve never had an issue reaching the required Threshold, but I also mulligan aggressively for dual/triple lands.</p>"
    },
