    "guide": {
      "overview": "<p>This is the Gothic updated version of my Deathspeaker deck that won at the West Virginia Courtesan Cup Qualifier back in 2024 and got 2nd at the FL Cup Qualifier. I didn't update it for Arthurian Legends due to me not thinking enough was added to make it worth playing, and other life situations that caused me to not be able to play as much. However, in Gothic, my passion has been rekindled and I think the deck may have a chance.</p><p><br></p><p>I haven't tested the deck much yet and am thinking about running either Harbinger or Savior as the avatar. Harbinger seems better for early game, whereas Savior seems better for late game, so more testing needs to be done first.</p><p><br></p><p>There's a lot of Cemetery hate in Gothic, so if those cards see a lot of play, I may switch to a more Earth focused build that uses Wormellow Tump and maybe Key to the City.</p><p><br></p><p>I've decided not to run Deathspeaker as there wasn't much added in Gothic to synergize with it and the Spirits build, but that doesn't mean it can't be done, I just figured I'd try some other things first. I'll try to keep this list updated as I playtest.</p><p><br></p><p>The original deck list with a link to the deck tech video that won the Qualifier is here: https://curiosa.io/decks/cmj31b5mn0i3z1kfo6zmn2bnc?tab=view</p>"
    },
