    "guide": {
      "overview": "<p>Utilise the power of [[Avatar of Earth]] to crush your foes. [[Avatar of Earth]] is currently the avatar with the highest potential power in the game! You can realistically get your Avatar up to 5 or 6 power when attacking relatively easily, particularly if you utilise [[Atlas Wanderers]] and [[Earthquake]] to rearrange your opponent's sites so they're nestled in amongst your earth sites.</p><p><br></p><p>The deck utilises the most efficient minions earth has to offer in [[Autumn Unicorn]], [[Pudge Butcher]] and [[Atlas Wanderers]], as well as some utility minions in [[Kettletop Leprechaun]], and some other efficient beaters / Root Spider removal / Roots of Yggdrasil insurance in [[Bluecap Knockersl]].</p><p><br></p><p>[[Holy Ground]] helps keep the aggro decks at bay. Your [[Common Sense]] toolkit includes mobility spells in [[Blink]] and [[Grapple Shot]], direct damage from [[Magic Missiles]] and [[Duel]], artifact and aura removal from [[Dispel]], creature or artifact removal from [[Bury]].</p><p><br></p><p>Earth alone can have a hard time closing the game out, which is where [[Rhongomyniad]], [[Rolling Boulder]], [[Duel]], [[Magic Missiles]] and [[Stone Rain]] can help you catch the more evasive avatars trying to run from you.</p><p><br></p><p>All in all, you're trying to use efficiency, raw power and some tactical flexibility to get the job done!</p>"
    },
    "hasPrimer": true
