    "guide": {
      "overview": "<h1><strong><u>\"Thank You, Come Again!\"</u></strong></h1><h2><strong>Sorcerer: <em>[🔥/💧]</em> Midrange Combo Brew</strong></h2><h3><strong><em>Sneaky Combos That Lead To HEAVY DAMAGE!</em></strong></h3><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>NEW SEASON NEW ME! [TESTING]</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><strong><em>*My first attempt at a Fire + Water brew without Elementalist.</em></strong></p><p><strong><em>Decided rather than going for a more straight forward aggro build with Fire that I would use the Fire for Movement/Chip Damage early.</em></strong></p><p><strong><em>Also instead of using Water for control, I wanted to use Water for more pressure with the combos that can be done.*</em></strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>The key is to get some damage in where you can while also minimizing damage as much as possible.</strong></p><p><strong>Pick and choose where to play your Dragons and Cats early to extend the game.</strong></p><p><strong>Play your spellcasters up front to cast removal that's too far for your Avatar.</strong></p><p><strong>This brew plays heavy combos around 5-6 mana, so it's best to get setup by then to hit big OTK combos when least expected.</strong></p><p><strong>The Cores really help when they are drawn early to get those combos going sooner rather than later and Philosopher's Stone will forever be a blessing.</strong></p><p><strong>You don't need to OTK in this build to win.. however there are multiple options when it comes to hitting them in game.</strong></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><h3><strong>MVP CARDS</strong></h3><ol><li><a href=\"https://curiosa.io/cards#search=eyJxdWVyeSI6Inlva2FpIGthcHBhcyIsInNldCI6IioiLCJmaWx0ZXJzIjpbXSwiY3NvcnQiOiJyZWxldmFuY2UiLCJkc29ydCI6InJlbGV2YW5jZSIsImRpdmlkZXIiOiJhbGwiLCJhdmF0YXIiOiIqIn0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Yokai Kappas</a></li><li><a href=\"https://curiosa.io/cards#search=eyJxdWVyeSI6IkhlbHBmdWwgSG9iIiwic2V0IjoiKiIsImZpbHRlcnMiOltdLCJjc29ydCI6InJlbGV2YW5jZSIsImRzb3J0IjoicmVsZXZhbmNlIiwiZGl2aWRlciI6ImFsbCIsImF2YXRhciI6IioifQ\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Helpful Hob</a></li><li><a href=\"https://curiosa.io/cards#search=eyJxdWVyeSI6IlN3b3JkIGFuZCBTaGllbGQiLCJzZXQiOiIqIiwiZmlsdGVycyI6W10sImNzb3J0IjoicmVsZXZhbmNlIiwiZHNvcnQiOiJyZWxldmFuY2UiLCJkaXZpZGVyIjoiYWxsIiwiYXZhdGFyIjoiKiJ9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Sword and Shield</a></li><li><a href=\"https://curiosa.io/cards#search=eyJxdWVyeSI6IldhcnAgU3Bhc20iLCJzZXQiOiIqIiwiZmlsdGVycyI6W10sImNzb3J0IjoicmVsZXZhbmNlIiwiZHNvcnQiOiJyZWxldmFuY2UiLCJkaXZpZGVyIjoiYWxsIiwiYXZhdGFyIjoiKiJ9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Warp Spasm</a></li><li><a href=\"https://curiosa.io/cards#search=eyJxdWVyeSI6IkxlYXAgQXR0YWNrIiwic2V0IjoiKiIsImZpbHRlcnMiOltdLCJjc29ydCI6InJlbGV2YW5jZSIsImRzb3J0IjoicmVsZXZhbmNlIiwiZGl2aWRlciI6ImFsbCIsImF2YXRhciI6IioifQ\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Leap Attack</a></li></ol><p><br></p><p>Honorable Mentions</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://curiosa.io/cards#search=eyJxdWVyeSI6IlBsYWd1ZSBvZiBGcm9ncyIsInNldCI6IioiLCJmaWx0ZXJzIjpbXSwiY3NvcnQiOiJyZWxldmFuY2UiLCJkc29ydCI6InJlbGV2YW5jZSIsImRpdmlkZXIiOiJhbGwiLCJhdmF0YXIiOiIqIn0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Plague of Frogs</a></li><li><a href=\"https://curiosa.io/cards#search=eyJxdWVyeSI6IkJvdWRpY2NhIiwic2V0IjoiKiIsImZpbHRlcnMiOltdLCJjc29ydCI6InJlbGV2YW5jZSIsImRzb3J0IjoicmVsZXZhbmNlIiwiZGl2aWRlciI6ImFsbCIsImF2YXRhciI6IioifQ\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Boudicca</a></li><li><a href=\"https://curiosa.io/cards#search=eyJxdWVyeSI6IlJ1bGVyIG9mIFRodWwiLCJzZXQiOiIqIiwiZmlsdGVycyI6W10sImNzb3J0IjoicmVsZXZhbmNlIiwiZHNvcnQiOiJyZWxldmFuY2UiLCJkaXZpZGVyIjoiYWxsIiwiYXZhdGFyIjoiKiJ9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Ruler of Thul</a></li></ul><p><br></p><h3><strong>MVP COMBOS</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Yokai Kappas + Sword and Shield + Warp Spasm</strong> <em>(This combo here is an OTK that can be done on Turn 6 so long as you have a Water Site in hand.)</em></li><li><strong>Yokai Kappas + Helpful Hob + [Water Site]</strong> <em>(This combo feels much better with a Sword and Shield equipped, but 9 damage for 4 mana seems really good.)</em></li><li><strong>Sir Agravaine + Plague of Frogs</strong> <em>(This combo can OTK you if you're not ready.. Play the Frogs and Swing with them at Leader/Minions and let Agravaine Jump in for 3 every time a frog swings. This feels good with Jihad on board.)</em></li><li><strong>Boudicca + Plague of Frogs</strong> <em>(This is another one that can sneak up on you if you're not ready. Door by turn 4 potentially.)</em></li><li><strong>Leap Attack + Any 5 Power Minion </strong><em>(Every time I hit this it feels SO good! Having the Sword and Shield helps the 3 Power minions in the build get there so they don't feel left out.)</em></li><li><strong>Warp Spasm + Any 5 Power Minion + Helpful Hob</strong> <em>(BIG CHONKY BOY DAMAGE!)</em></li></ul><p><br></p><h3><strong>Death's Door Finishers</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Heat Ray/Firebolts<em> </em></strong><em>being the obvious ones if in position with your Avatar, Adept Illusionist, or Morgana le Fey.</em></li><li><strong><em>Fire Breathing </em></strong><em>due to having said spellcasters above along with 6 Beast/Dragon Targets to cast from is a solid game winner in here. (Can be cast by the frog tokens too.)</em></li><li><strong><em>Colicky Dragonette</em></strong><em> can shoot for 1 to win the game when placed in the right spot.</em></li><li><strong><em>Ring of Morrigan </em></strong><em>by being close enough and playing any card to win the game seems fair.</em></li><li><strong><em>Minor Explosion</em></strong><em> just in case..</em></li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong><em>There are plenty of combos that can be done with other cards in the build, the ones above are just some that I built the deck around and some I've performed in game that I actually liked. </em></strong></p><p><strong><em>Some really good cards in here but there is also some sleeper cards in the brew which I'm also a fan of!</em></strong></p><p><strong><em>All in all this deck has been really fun and pretty consistent.</em></strong></p><p><strong><em>Will update periodically with changes.</em></strong></p><p><br></p><p><em>*Please let me know if you happen to run the deck and how it goes in the comments.</em></p><p><em>Thanks in advance.* 1-800-DID-iCOOK?</em></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><h1><strong><em><u>Accolades &amp; Notes</u></em></strong></h1><p><br></p><h3><strong><em>12/28* - WENT <u>5 - 0</u> IN THE SORCERERS AT THE CORE EU CONSTRUCTED LEAGUE [FLAWLESS VICTORY]</em></strong></h3><p><br></p><p><strong><em>1/8 - Wanted to try 1 Minor Explosion out, dropped the Stormy Seas to the side for now... might revert back.</em></strong></p><p><br></p><h3><strong><em>1/8* - WENT <u>4 - 0</u> TO WIN A 20 PLAYER LOCAL TOURNAMENT @ Gamers Guild (AZ)</em></strong><em> </em><strong><em>[CERTIFIED]</em></strong></h3><p><br></p><p><strong><em>1/9 - Dropping a Wizard's Den for the Mirage, one is fine.. right?</em></strong></p><p><br></p><h3><strong><em>1/22* - WENT <u>3 - 0 </u>TO WIN A 12 PLAYER LOCAL TOURNAMENT @ Gamers Guild (AZ)</em></strong></h3><p><strong><em>I missed last weeks locals so it felt good to get back out there tonight and continue a win streak with the brew in tournament play.</em></strong></p><p><strong><em>There was a game where I had 14 bodies on board by turn 4 which is actually INSANE!!</em></strong></p><p><strong><em>I turn 2 played Adept Illusionist, turn 3 played Tadpole Pool for 3 frogs and casted Plague of Frogs (10 fkn FROGS baby!) then tapped to bring out the other Illusionist,</em></strong></p><p><strong><em>turn 4 played Brother Knight and grabbed his brother from the deck for 14 bodies! [SO MUCH FUN!]</em></strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong><em>﻿</em></strong></p>"
    },
