    "guide": {
      "overview": "<p><strong>Gameplay Notes:</strong></p><p><br></p><p>Dragonlord to partner with Caelestis.</p><p><br></p><p>Threshold focus is Air/Fire. This may need more fire sites, particularly for Ignis). If including, never hold a Mix Terra in opening hand. Don’t hold any of the single ordinary spells in opening hand. Use Common Sense. Don’t hold Draco Corvus in opening hand.</p><p><br></p><p>Prioritize Mirror Realm &amp; Valley to ensure you have exactly: 3 air, 3 fire and 2 earth. Only lastly consider a 3rd earth if playing Talamh.</p><p><br></p><p>Princess to get the right Mix.</p><p><br></p><p>Need Paliburrie Bats in deck or sideboard for spiders. Blink can also help.</p><p><br></p><p>—————————————</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Deck Design Notes:</strong></p><p><br></p><p>Initial test was with Elementalist out of fear of threashold, but she petered out too quickly.</p><p><br></p><p>Needs more early draw to get the dragons while building up mana.</p><p><br></p><p>geyser might be a better solution for spiders than bats.</p><p><br></p><p>last consideration is to replace a colicky with Talamh. Threshold is the challenge.</p><p><br></p><p>———————————————</p><p><br></p><p>Post Gothic</p><p><br></p><p>add Draconian Bonekite! Replace Xeraphine Konrul? In fact, this needs to become the partner dragon and include Poisonous Dagger!</p>"
    },
