    "guide": {
      "overview": "<p>The overall goal is to abuse the synergy between Hamlet and Sylvan Splendor, cast a minion for 0/1, and draw a card, repeat until you dont see a cheap minion, cast assorted animals and grab some beasts, and continue the value train. get close to the enemy avatar and close the game with the swarm. anytime you cast a 0 cost minion, feel free to ward it. There is basically a ordinary 1 drop for every edgecase, playing against graves, grab a Carrion Beetles. Need to answer a ring of morrigan/core, Thieving Magpie. Need to summon those things on the opponents board, Ominous Owl/Spore Spouts. Sly Fox.</p><p>Goat is actually the GOAT, if you already have an established board, you can play him, ward him, swing, re-ward, swing, re-ward, etc.</p><p>[[Lady Iseult]] adds another layer of combo potential with the [[Ring of Morigan]] it can cause plenty of infinite loops, notably your opponent will need to fully commit to dealing 20 damage to you in a given turn to door you.</p><p><br></p><p>Ward the Tufted Turtle, its funny, if it would take damage you can have its effect protect the ward. Shield maidens helps protect any/all wards from being pinged off. Goat protects all wards, and if you have shield maidens near it, theres a chance you can save its wards too :D</p><p><br></p><p>There are a lot of infinte combos in this list, mostly involving: lady issuelt, hamlet, sylvan splendor, horn of caerleon, Pnakotic Manuscript,</p>"
    },
