    "guide": {
      "overview": "<p>I think it goes without saying at this point but you always want to go first with Sorcerer decks. Get to the point where you can consistently draw and play two spells per turn and you're in business. Charge is very strong in Sorcery since there isn't much instant speed interaction. This deck was recently updated to accommodate for the resurgence of Earth Air Midrange. If you see Sorcerer across the table then you absolutely need a fast starting hand to set the tempo before it gets set against you. The Sorcerer and Druid matchups can go long so the artifacts in this deck will add a lot of value to your gameplan over the course of the game.</p><p>Use Sinkhole to deal with Pebbled Paths (stops charge), Free City, Gnome Hollows, opposing Sinkhole/Roots, and Perilous Bridge. Use Great Famine and Sand Worm to combat Root Spider and fetch buried artifacts when necessary. Use Sir Pellinore to easily take out big butts like Sir Galahad or Infernal Legion.</p><p>I brought Infiltrate back in along with Chaos Twister among other things because we absolutely have to be able to take care of 5 power minions like Pudge Butcher as soon as they come out. Yes a well placed Root Spider can take them back but we buy a turn to move out of the way at least.</p><p>Courtesan Thais is amazing at finishing out a game or stopping any forward momentum your opponent starts to gain.</p><p>Peasant Revolt is one of the best way to punish a 3 color or 4 color deck or a deck that leans heavily on Cores etc.</p>"
    },
